article.description: Ohio rallies for 82-75 win over Miami (Ohio)
article.headline: Ohio rallies for 82-75 win over Miami (Ohio)
article.linkText: Ohio rallies for 82-75 win over Miami (Ohio)
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Nick Kellogg pumped in 27 points and Travis Wilkins added 23, both career highs, to lead Ohio to an 82-75 win over Miami (Ohio) on Saturday. Trailing 47-32 at the break, Ohio (17-6, 7-3 Mid-American Conference) rallied huge in the second half with a 22-5 run that included a trio of Wilkins 3-pointers. The lead went back and forth before the Bobcats took control with back-to-back 3-pointers from Kellogg to take a 68-65 lead they would pad and protect over the final 3 minutes. Maurice Ndour contributed 14 points and eight rebounds for the Bobcats, who hit 29 of 55 from field (53 percent) and were 11 of 29 from 3-point range. Miami (9-12, 5-5) hit 25 of 53 overall but was held to just 12.5 percent shooting in the second half while being outscored 50-28. Will Felder and Bill Edwards led the Redhawks with 19 points each.
